      "writtenOn": "2018-09-13T19:52:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this is too aggressive, the main thing to avoid is if the tempDir is empty or doesn\u0027t contain any directory components.  We want to avoid deleting \"/\" or \"C:\\\".  Maybe make sure that we have at least one directory in addition to the root?  So C:\\ \u003d invalid, C:\\Temp \u003d valid, and similarly / \u003d invalid, /tmp \u003d valid.\n\nAlso canonicalize/normalize it so that a path can\u0027t be \"C:\\Users\\something\\Temp\\..\\..\\..\\\"",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2552,
        "startChar": 4,
